title: IOC disqualifies Ukrainian skeleton racer Vladyslav Heraskevych over helmet | ABC NEWS
description: Vladyslav Heraskevych has been disqualified from the Milano Cortina Winter Games over the use of a helmet depicting Ukrainian athletes killed in the Russia-Ukraine War.  The International Olympic Committee said it made its decision to disqualify the Ukrainian "with regret". Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskyy has voiced support for Heraskevych  and slammed the IOC. title: Ousted Liberal leader Sussan Ley to resign from parliament | ABC NEWS
description: Former Liberal leader Sussan Ley has confirmed she will resign from parliament, after losing the Liberal leadership ballot.   She secured 17 votes in today's special Liberal party room meeting, while Angus Taylor secured 34 votes.   Ms Ley said she respected the decision made by the party room.   She thanked the colleagues who supported her and said she had "no hard feelings" for those who didn't support her.   Ms Ley said she will spend the next few weeks speaking with voters in her electorate before handing her resignation to the Speaker.   "It is important that the leader gets clean air … more important than ever," she said.   In her statement to the media, Ms Ley expressed her "gratitude to the Liberal party".  "There is no doubt it has been a challenging time to lead the party after we suffered the worst defeat in 81 years," she said.    "It has been tough, at times very tough." title: Turnbull says Liberal Party needs to 'stop living in a right-wing populist bubble' | ABC NEWS
description: Malcolm Turnbull tells David Speers, Patricia Karvelas and Melissa Clarke that the Liberal Party needs to move back to the centre and Angus Taylor is not the answer to the party’s problems. He says the LNP needs to start talking about the economy and deliver detailed plans for tax reform and housing affordability. The former prime minister says they need to stop 'living in a populist bubble’ and stop doing things for 'soundbites on Sky News.'
